The paper deals with the development of an under-approximate relational logic for reasoning about program behaviours, which falls under the category of logic and verification (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the application of the logic in identifying security vulnerabilities, which could potentially fall under the categories of programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Hoare logic, which is a formal method for program verification and could fall under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
